    <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
        Privacy notice
    </h1>

    <p>The Ministry of Justice (MOJ) is committed to the protection and security of your personal information.</p>
    <p>This privacy notice describes how we collect and use personal information during and after your relationship with
        us, in accordance with data protection law. This notice will be updated regularly.
    </p>
    <p>MOJ is the data controller for the personal data used for the purposes of providing suitable residential
        placements for high-risk offenders in a structured environment to support rehabilitation and resettlement in the
        community. </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">The types of personal data we process</h2>

    <p>We currently collect and use the following information:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>Full name</li>
        <li>Date of birth</li>
        <li>Address history</li>
        <li>Contact details</li>
        <li>Employment details & recourse to funding</li>
    </ul>
    <p> We also collect special categories of information, such as:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>Medical or healthcare</li>
        <li>Disability or specific condition</li>
        <li>Religion/religious beliefs</li>
        <li>Citizenship status</li>
        <li>Age</li>
        <li>Nationality</li>
        <li>Racial or ethnic origin</li>
        <li>Gender</li>
        <li>Criminal history</li>
        <li>Criminal records</li>
        <li>Drug test results</li>
        <li>Sex, gender and sexual orientation</li>
        <li>Veteran status</li>
        <li>Care leaver status</li>
        <li>Relationship status</li>
        <li>Caring or parental responsibilities</li>
        <li>Criminal convictions</li>
        <li>Personal connections to geographic areas</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How we collect your personal information and why we have it</h2>
    <p>Most of the personal information processed is to enable the service to be used to:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>complete and submit an online application for CAS-1/Approved Premise accommodation</li>
        <li>assess and make a decision on suitability for placement in CAS-1/Approved Premise accommodation</li>
        <li>place a person in an Approved Premise which meets their individual need</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We also receive personal information indirectly, from the following sources in the following scenarios if
        available:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>Common Platform for Crown Prosecution Service documentation</li>
        <li>NDelius for information on your bail status and probation history</li>
        <li>Nomis or Digital Prison Services (DPS) for information on your offence history</li>
        <li>Prison drug and alcohol provider, mental health in-reach and healthcare team about your health needs</li>
        <li>Community Liaison & Diversion reports</li>
        <li>Social workers for information relating to safeguarding</li>
        <li>OASys for information on your level of risk to yourself, public, known adults, staff and children</li>
        <li>HMPPS staff including your community probation practitioner (CPP), also known as community offender manager
            (COM), for information on your previous or current probation supervision
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p>We use the personal data we receive in order to:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>make an assessment of suitability for Approved Premises accommodation</li>
        <li>match people to an appropriate Approved Premise accommodation</li>
        <li>monitor whether applicants with certain characteristics (for example, gender, sexual orientation, age,
            ethnic background, faith, and disability) have different success rates in being accepted into Approved
            Premises to ensure that no group is treated unfairly
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p>We may share this information with:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>HMPPS Performance Hub</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Under the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR), the lawful bases we rely on for processing this
        information are:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list">
        <li>(b) We have a contractual obligation</li>
        <li>(e) We need it to perform a public task</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The legal bases on which the MOJ processes special categories of information you have provided, is based on:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>the processing being necessary for the MOJ in the ﬁeld of employment, social security and social protection
            law
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">International data transfers </h2>
    <p>There are no international transfers. </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How we store your personal data</h2>

    <p>Personal information is stored securely and in accordance with the <a class="govuk-link"
                                                                      href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/record-retention-and-disposition-schedules"
                                                                      target="_blank">MOJ data retention schedule (opens
            in new tab)</a>. At the end of this period your information is disposed of.</p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Your rights</h2>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>You have the right to ask us for copies of your personal information.</li>
        <li>You have the right to ask us to rectify personal information you think is inaccurate. You also have the
            right to ask us to complete information you think is incomplete.
        </li>
        <li>You have the right to ask us to restrict the processing of your personal information in certain
            circumstances.
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>Depending on the lawful basis on which your personal data is being processed, not all rights will apply.</p>
    <p>You are not required to pay any charge for exercising your rights. If you make a request, we have 1 month to
        respond to you.</p>
